#Works Cited

“How to...use Twitter for academic research,” by Margaret Adolphus (http://www.emeraldgrouppublishing.com/research/guides/management/twitter.htm)

“Where to get Twitter data for academic research,” by Justin Littman (https://gwu-libraries.github.io/sfm-ui/posts/2017-09-14-twitter-data)

“5 Terrific Twitter Research Tools,” by Ben Parr (https://mashable.com/2009/05/03/twitter-research-tools/#SRm2MXdFN8qw)

“Using Twitter as a data source: an overview of social media research tools (updated for 2017),” by Wasim Ahmed (http://blogs.lse.ac.uk/impactofsocialsciences/2017/05/08/using-twitter-as-a-data-source-an-overview-of-social-media-research-tools-updated-for-2017/)

“Higher education scholars’ participation and practices on Twitter,” by G. Veletsianos (http://www.veletsianos.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/scholars_on_twitter_veletsianos.pdf)

"Some Thoughts on Ethics and DocNow," by Bergis Jules (https://news.docnow.io/some-thoughts-on-ethics-and-docnow-d19cfec427f2)

"AoIR Ethics Guidelines: DocSocData 2" a round of of conversations on ethical twitter archives by Ed Summers (https://news.docnow.io/aoir-ethics-guidelines-docsocdata-2-a4344b93a12d)

"Geographic Dissection of the Twitter Network," by Juhi Kulshrestha, Farshad Kooti, Ashkan Nikravesh, and Krishna P. Gummadi (https://people.mpi-sws.org/~farshad/geographic_dissection.pdf)

"You Are Where You Tweet: A Content-Based Approach to Geo-locating Twitter Users" (http://faculty.cs.tamu.edu/caverlee/pubs/cheng10cikm.pdf)

"Why We Twitter: Understanding Microblogging Usage and Communities" (https://ebiquity.umbc.edu/_file_directory_/papers/369.pdf)

"Geography of Twitter Networks" (http://takhteyev.org/papers/Takhteyev-Wellman-Gruzd-2010.pdf)

"Who Says What to Whom on Twitter" (http://www.wwwconference.org/proceedings/www2011/proceedings/p705.pdf)

